# FlipCards-with-css3
working on transforms and transform-style properties to build a flip card 
=========>include css file flipCard.css in your html 
steps to add flip cards to your html
1.wrap your flipCards in a container div with class 'flip-cards'
2.each flip card will be wrapped in a div with class 'flip-container'
3.in flip-container classed div place a div with class 'card' and make childs of this div,one with class 'front' for front 
of card and other one with class 'back' for back of the card
4.inside these divs with classes 'front' and 'back' put text or any image you would like to be placed on the card
5.repeat step 2 to make multiple cards 
To change the size of cards update .flip-container class in your css
To update front and back of cards update 'front' and 'back' classes in your css

code snippet -----------
<div class="flip-cards">
  <!--first card -->
<div class="flip-container">
<div class="card">
<div class="front">
<!--some text or image here  As you wish-->
</div>
<div class="back">
<!--some text or image here  As you wish-->
</div>
</div>
</div>
  <!-- second card -->
  <div class="flip-container">
<div class="card">
<div class="front">
<!--some text or image here  As you wish-->
</div>
<div class="back">
<!--some text or image here  As you wish-->
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
